data.enText: to work together with sb in order to produce or achieve sth

data.chText: 这些年来我们合作搞了许多项目。
data.enText: We have collaborated on many projects over the years.

data.chText: 她同意与他合作撰写她的传记。
data.enText: She agreed to collaborate with him in writing her biography.

data.chText: 世界各地的研究人员正在合作培育一种新的疫苗。
data.enText: Researchers around the world are collaborating to develop a new vaccine.
to help the enemy who has taken control of your country during a war

simple_means.memory_skill: col 共同 + labor 劳动，工作 + ate 表动词 → 一起工作 → 合作

ex.chText: 两国正在一个人造卫星项目上进行合作。
ex.enText: The two countries are collaborating on a satellite project.

ex.chText: 我们学院愿意就这个项目同贵校合作。
ex.enText: Our college would like to collaborate with yours on this program.

synonyms.bx: 多指在科学、艺术等领域中与某人或某组织合作，常后接介词with/on。

ex.chText: 他们的工会头头跟管理层串通一气。
ex.enText: Their union leaders colluded with the management.

ex.chText: 这两家公司合伙欺骗政府。
ex.enText: The two firms colluded to cheat the government.

synonyms.bx: 指私下勾结，共谋欺诈或不法之事，常后接介词 with。

ex.chText: 他们拒绝与一家美国公司合作。
ex.enText: They refused to cooperate with an American company.

ex.chText: 双方同意合作修建这条铁路。
ex.enText: Both sides agreed to cooperate on building this railway.

synonyms.bx: 指为实现共同目标而进行合作，常后接介词 with。

tr: work together on a common enterprise of project
example: The soprano and the pianist did not get together very well
We joined forces with another research group
he collaborated with the Nazis when they occupied Paris

value.def: When one person or group collaborates with another, they work together, especially on a book or on some research.

example.ex: He collaborated with his son Michael on the English translation of a text on food production...
example.tran: 他和儿子迈克尔合作，把一篇介绍食品生产的文章译成了英文。

example.ex: The government is urging Japan's firms to collaborate with foreigners.
example.tran: 政府正在督促日本的公司进行更多的海外合作。

example.ex: ...a place where professionals and amateurs collaborated in the making of music...
example.tran: 一个专业人士和业余爱好者合作创作音乐的地方

example.ex: The two men met and agreed to collaborate.
example.tran: 这两个人见了面，并同意进行合作。

gramarinfo.label: Also pl-n V to-inf, V <l>with</l> n to-inf

value.tran: 合作，协作(尤指著书或做研究)

value.def: If someone collaborates with an enemy that is occupying their country during a war, they help them.

example.ex: He was accused of having collaborated with the secret police.
example.tran: 他被控与秘密警察勾结。
